ork? Didn't you see he was failing. Was he in a class with rowdy kids. Did the teacher complain to you but you gave her a gobful? &#10;The things I mention in the second paragraph are some of the reasons why kids are failing, basically, parents have low expectations of their kids and they transmit this at school. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="614" language="en" documentId="762" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="smellthecoffee" date="07 January 2011 11:39am" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://discussion.theguardian.com/comment-permalink/9050235" topic="homeschooling" thumbsUp="11" thumbsDown="0" origId="762" notes="" title="Why I home school my children"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="209"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="210" end="433"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="47" sofa="1" begin="434" end="614"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39 43 47"/></xmi:XMI>